  "doc_id": "13592",
  "text": "The vacuum state for the static geometry, which is known as the Boulware vacuum, has neither incoming nor outgoing radiation at large distances. It is given by the condition β(u) = 0 , γ(v) = 0 (2.11) in the vacuum energy-momentum tensor (2.4)-(2.7). It is well-known that the vacuum energy-momentum tensor of the Boulware vacuum diverges at the horizon in the perturbative calculation around the Schwarzschild background. But, in fact, no divergence appears if the back-reaction of the vacuum energy is properly taken into account [CITATION_1] .",
